1 Section 1101. The defendant, in an action for the recovery of
2 money only, may, at any time before the trial, serve upon the
3 plaintiff or his attorney an offer, in writing, to allow judgment to
4 be taken against him for the sum specified therein. If the
5 plaintiff accept the offer and give notice thereof to the defendant
6 or his attorney, within five days after the offer was served, the
7 offer, and an affidavit that the notice of acceptance was delivered
8 within the time limited, may be filed by the plaintiff, or the
9 defendant may file the acceptance, with a copy of the offer,
10 verified by affidavit; and in either case, the offer and acceptance
11 shall be noted in the journal, and judgment shall be rendered
12 accordingly. If the notice of acceptance be not given in the period
13 limited, the offer shall be deemed withdrawn, and shall not be given
14 in evidence or mentioned on the trial. If the plaintiff fails to
15 obtain judgment for more than was offered by the defendant, he shall
16 pay the defendant’s costs from the time of the offer
17 A. MAKING AN OFFER; JUDGMENT ON AN ACCEPTED OFFER.
18 At least seven (7) days before a date set for trial, a party
19 defending against a claim may serve on an opposing party an offer to
20 allow judgment on specified terms. If the opposing party accepts
21 the offer, acceptance shall be made within five (5) days after
22 service of the offer and either party may then file the offer and
23 notice of acceptance plus proof of service. The court clerk shall
24 then enter judgment.
SB453 HFLR Page 3
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 B. UNACCEPTED OFFER.
2 An unaccepted offer is considered withdrawn but shall not
3 preclude a later offer. Evidence of an unaccepted offer is not
4 admissible except in a proceeding to determine costs.
5 C. OFFER AFTER LIABILITY IS DETERMINED.
6 When the liability of one party to another has been established
7 but the extent of liability remains to be determined, the party held
8 liable may make an offer of judgment. Any such offer shall be
9 served no fewer than seven (7) days prior to the date set for a
10 hearing to determine the extent of liability.
11 D. PAYING COSTS AFTER AN UNACCEPTED OFFER.
12 1. If the judgment the offeree obtains is less than or equal to
13 the unaccepted offer or the judgment is for the offering party, the
14 offeree shall pay the litigation costs of the offeror incurred after
15 the offer was made. Litigation costs shall include recovery of all
16 allowable costs associated with the litigation process after the
17 offer was rejected including, but not limited to:
18 a. reasonable attorney fees, if otherwise permitted by
19 law,
20 b. court costs,
21 c. expert witness fees, and
22 d. interest to be set in accordance with Section 727.1 of
23 this title and assessed and collected as other costs
24 of the action.
SB453 HFLR Page 4
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 2. If the judgment the offeree obtains exceeds the offer of
2 judgment, the offeree shall be entitled to recover reasonable
3 attorney fees, court costs, and interest to the extent otherwise
4 permitted by law for the offeree’s claim.
5 3. For purposes of comparing the amount of a judgment with the
6 amount of an offer, any recoverable litigation costs shall not be
7 included in the amount of the compared judgment.
8 E. OFFER OF JUDGMENT LETTER.
9 An offer of judgment letter shall include the following:
10 1. The judgment offer amount;
11 2. If the offer of judgment is for part of the amount claimed
12 or part of the causes involved in the action, then specifically to
13 which cause or causes the offer of judgment applies;
14 3. If the offer includes attorney fees;
15 4. If the action involves multiple opposing parties, then to
16 which party the offer of judgment applies;
17 5. If the action involves multiple opposing parties and the
18 offer of judgement is for all parties, then specifically how much
19 each opposing party is to receive of the offer amount; and
20 6. The expiration date of the offer as determined pursuant to
21 subsection A of this section.
22 F. EFFECTIVENESS.
23 The provisions of this section shall be applicable to an action
24 filed on or after the effective date of this act.
